*Areas of high cumulative pressure tend to translate into areas of poor ecological condition. The first ground-truthing of marine ecosystem condition shows that pressure mapping is an effective proxy at broad national scales, but that finer scale pressure mapping can improve condition estimates. Increased monitoring, [further refinement of indicators and improved understanding of ecosystem responses to pressures are]{.mark} needed to support more accurate assessments of ecological condition ([key message C2](../key-messages/kmc2.qmd))*

![Maintaining marine ecosystems in good ecological condition is a key goal of ecosystem based management. © Eve Marshall, Triton Dive Charters](imgs/apr2017_Eve_Marshall_Triton_100_cropped.png)

\

## Ecological condition results

The condition map shows areas that are assessed to be in one of four categories of ecological condition: natural/near-natural, moderately modified, severely modified and very severely modified (Box 1). Critically modified areas were included in the severely modified category in this assessment. In South Africa's marine environment, critically modified components are only present in some shore ecosystem types, where (coastal development or ports) infrastructure has caused irreversible habitat loss.

![Map of ecological condition showing the spatial distribution of marine benthopelagic and benthic areas in different ecological condition categories as calculated from cumulative pressures (see [@sec-approach] and [Majiedt et al. 2019](http://hdl.handle.net/20.500.12143/6372)).](imgs/condition_with_donut.png){#fig-condition_benthic .lightbox}

![Map of ecological condition showing the spatial distribution of marine pelagic areas in different ecological condition categories as calculated from cumulative pressures (see [@sec-approach].)](imgs/condition_pel_with_donut.png){#fig-condition_pelagic .lightbox}

\
Areas of very severely modified ecological condition in the benthopelagic and benthic ecosystems include the southwest Atlantic shelf edge, many inner shelf areas adjacent to the Western Cape, parts of the south coast and shelf, and multiple areas in the KwaZulu-Natal Bight [@fig-condition_benthic]. The ecological condition map for the marine realm was not updated for the 2025 NBA although some pressure layer updates have been underway.

![The Browns Bank Rocky Shelf is one of the marine ecosystem types with the greatest extent of very severe (84%) ecosystem modification. © SAEON](imgs/WCVS19_sTATION_4_292m_26.png)

The marine realm has relatively high proportions of areas in the natural/near-natural ecological condition (@fig-condition_benthic, @fig-condition_pelagic). However, ecosystem modification tends to be focused in pressure hotspots, usually linked to local characteristics such as high productivity, accessibility and valuable natural resources (such as bays, inner shelf and shelf edge areas), while large and often remote areas remain relatively lightly used and unmodified.


